 Step 3: Debounce component

 File: atari/src/main/scala/atari800/Debounce.scala (new, small utility)

 Per-signal debounce: 2-FF synchronizer (BufferCC) + per-bit counter. When input stable for ~20ms (2^20 cycles at 56.67 MHz ≈
 18.4ms), output updates. Default state: all-ones (pull-up, nothing pressed).

 class Debounce(width: Int, stableBits: Int = 20) extends Component {
   val io = new Bundle {
     val raw = in  Bits(width bits)
     val debounced = out Bits(width bits)
   }
   // per-bit: BufferCC sync, then counter-based stable detection
 }

